FOLKUNGA结婚。他们至少是4个儿子和2个女儿的父母。他去世于1347年3月18日在他的家乡。"},"hr":{"–18 March 1347":"–18. ožujka 1347.","–1326":"–1326","–1347":"–1347.","–1350":"–1350","1300–1350":"1300–1350","–1359":"–1359","–Male":"preminuo","–Female":"preminula","–1280":"–1280.","–1341":"–1341","5 June 1319":"5. lipnja 1319.","1341":"1341","1252":"1252","1350":"1350","1250":"1250","1280":"1280.","abt 1300":"oko 1300.","1359":"1359","1326":"1326","22 February 1341":"22. veljače 1341.","1347":"1347.","1323":"1323","1300":"1300","1266":"1266","18 March 1347":"18. ožujka 1347.","before 1280":"prije 1280.","1318":"1318","1306":"1306","Sweden":"Švedska"},"cs":{"–18 March 1347":"–18. března 1347","–1326":"–1326","–1347":"–1347","–1350":"–1350","1300–1350":"1300–1350","–1359":"–1359","–Male":"Zesnulý","–Female":"Zesnulá","–1280":"–1280","–1341":"–1341","5 June 1319":"5. června 1319","1341":"1341","1252":"1252","1350":"1350","1250":"1250","1280":"1280","abt 1300":"okolo 1300","1359":"1359","1326":"1326","22 February 1341":"22. února 1341","1347":"1347","1323":"1323","1300":"1300","1266":"1266","18 March 1347":"18. března 1347","before 1280":"před 1280","1318":"1318","1306":"1306","Sweden":"Švédsko"},"da":{"–18 March 1347":"–18. marts 1347","–1326":"–1326","–1347":"–1347","–1350":"–1350","1300–1350":"1300–1350","–1359":"–1359","–Male":"Afdød","–Female":"Afdød","–1280":"–1280","–1341":"–1341","5 June 1319":"5. juni 1319","1341":"1341","1252":"1252","1350":"1350","1250":"1250","1280":"1280","abt 1300":"omkring 1300","1359":"1359","1326":"1326","22 February 1341":"22. februar 1341","1347":"1347","1323":"1323","1300":"1300","1266":"1266","18 March 1347":"18. marts 1347","before 1280":"før 1280","1318":"1318","1306":"1306","Sweden":"Sverige"},"nl":{"–18 March 1347":"–18 maart 1347","–1326":"–1326","–1347":"–1347","–1350":"–1350","1300–1350":"1300–1350","–1359":"–1359","–Male":"Overleden","–Female":"Overleden","–1280":"–1280","–1341":"–1341","5 June 1319":"5 juni 1319","1341":"1341","1252":"1252","1350":"1350","1250":"1250","1280":"1280","abt 1300":"circa 1300","1359":"1359","1326":"1326","22 February 1341":"22 februari 1341","1347":"1347","1323":"1323","1300":"1300","1266":"1266","18 March 1347":"18 maart 1347","before 1280":"vóór 1280","1318":"1318","1306":"1306","Sweden":"Zweden"},"en":{"–18 March 1347":"–18 March 1347","–1326":"–1326","–1347":"–1347","–1350":"–1350","1300–1350":"1300–1350","–1359":"–1359","–Male":"Deceased","–Female":"Deceased","–1280":"–1280","–1341":"–1341","5 June 1319":"5 June 1319","1341":"1341","1252":"1252","1350":"1350","1250":"1250","1280":"1280","abt 1300":"about 1300","1359":"1359","1326":"1326","22 February 1341":"22 February 1341","1347":"1347","1323":"1323","1300":"1300","1266":"1266","18 March 1347":"18 March 1347","before 1280":"before 1280","1318":"1318","1306":"1306","Sweden":"Sweden","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Knut","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["from Old Norse <i>Knútr</i> ‘knot’, originally a byname given to a short, squat man.  King Knut  (  d. 1035 ) ruled over Denmark, Norway, and England in the 11th century; he is known in English as Canute. His great-nephew Knut (  d. 1086 ) was another king of Denmark; he was murdered by opponents of the laws enforcing payment of tithes to the Church and was canonized as a martyr. His nephew, also Knut (  d. 1131 ), was Duke of Schleswig and is also venerated as a martyr, although for what reason is not clear."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Jönsson","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Scandinavian Nils, Lars, Lennart, Thor, Alf, Anders, Arni, Erik, Jorgen, Mats, Olafur, Per.","Swedish: patronymic from the personal name <i>Jon</i>, Scandinavian form of   John  . Compare   Jonson   2.","English: variant of   Johnson  , although this form of the English name may have died out in Britain."],"variants":[{"name":"John","meanings":["Contracted form of Old French <i>Jo(h)anne</i>, from Latin <i>Io(h)anna</i> (  see  Joanna  ). In England this was the usual feminine form of   John   from the Middle English period onwards and was extremely popular, but in the 16th and 17th centuries it steadily lost ground to   Jane .  It was strongly revived in the first part of the 20th century, partly under the influence of  George Bernard Shaw's  play St Joan (  1923 ), based on the life of  Joan of Arc  (  1412–31 ). Claiming to be guided by the voices of the saints, she persuaded the French dauphin to defy the occupying English forces and have himself crowned, and she led the French army that raised the siege of Orleans in  1429 . The following year she was captured by the Burgundians and sold to the English, and a year later she was burned at the stake for witchcraft at the age of 18 or 19. Her story has captured the imagination of many writers, and she is variously portrayed as a national and political hero, a model of apolitical straightforwardness and honesty, and a religious heroine. She was canonized in  1920 . More recent influences have included the American film actress  Joan Crawford  (  1908–77 , born  Lucille le Sueur ), the British actress  Joan Collins  (  b. 1933 ), the American comedienne  Joan Rivers  (  b. 1933 ), and the West Indian pop singer  Joan Armatrading  (  b. 1950 )."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1357046,"age":22,"year":"1250","julianDay":2177614,"description":"King Eriksson died. Valdemar crowned King. Birger Jarl declared regent until Valdemar is of age.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1702074,"age":24,"year":"1252","julianDay":2178344,"title":"Earliest Mention of Stockholm","description":"The earliest known recorded history of the city of Stockholm is in Norse sagas as Agnafit which dates to 1252. The city rose to prominence due to Baltic trade. Stockholm is now the most populous urban area in the region.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1357047,"age":38,"year":"1266","julianDay":2183458,"description":"King Valdemar overthrown by brothers.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1702075,"age":78,"year":"1306","julianDay":2198067,"title":"The Hatuna Games","description":"A conflict on September 29, 1306, between Birger, King of Sweden, and his brothers, the dukes Eric Magnusson and Valdemar Magnusson is known as The Hatuna Games. The brothers arrived to a party late in the night at King Birger's estate. The dukes captured and imprisoned Birger and his wife in Nykoping Castle's dungeon. Duke Eric then gained power over Sweden.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1357048,"age":90,"year":"1318","julianDay":2202450,"description":"Peasants revolted against King.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1357049,"age":95,"year":"1323","julianDay":2204276,"description":"Sweden and Russia establish border.","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"Knut Jönsson Aspenäs was born in Sweden as the son of Johan Filipsson Aspenäs and Ingeborg Svantepolksdotter. He married Katarina Bengtsdotter FOLKUNGA on 5 June 1319. They were the parents of at least 4 sons and 2 daughters. He died on 18 March 1347, in his hometown."},"et":{"–18 March 1347":"–18. märts 1347","–1326":"–1326","–1347":"–1347","–1350":"–1350","1300–1350":"1300–1350","–1359":"–1359","–Male":"Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","–1280":"–1280","–1341":"–1341","5 June 1319":"5. juuni 1319","1341":"1341","1252":"1252","1350":"1350","1250":"1250","1280":"1280","abt 1300":"umbes 1300","1359":"1359","1326":"1326","22 February 1341":"22. veebruar 1341","1347":"1347","1323":"1323","1300":"1300","1266":"1266","18 March 1347":"18. märts 1347","before 1280":"enne 1280","1318":"1318","1306":"1306","Sweden":"Rootsi"},"fi":{"–18 March 1347":"–18. maaliskuuta 1347","–1326":"–1326","–1347":"–1347","–1350":"–1350","1300–1350":"1300–1350","–1359":"–1359","–Male":"Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","–1280":"–1280","–1341":"–1341","5 June 1319":"5. kesäkuuta 1319","1341":"1341","1252":"1252","1350":"1350","1250":"1250","1280":"1280","abt 1300":"noi